import { useState } from "react" import { useHistory } from "react-router" function NewPlaceForm() { const history = useHistory() const [place, setPlace] = useState({ name: '', pic: '', city: '', state: '', cuisines: '' }) async function handleSubmit(e) { e.preventDefault() await fetch(`http://localhost:5000/places`, { method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }, body: JSON.stringify(place) }) history.push('/places') } return (
